Serie A side will have to fight PSG for Spurs star. So it seems as clubs launch bids to snatch away the EPL star. Juventus are hoping to make a late push for Tottenham’s Christian Eriksen.
The Express claims the Serie A champions have joined PSG in hoping to land the midfielder before Monday’s deadline.
In the same strides, Rangers attempted to sign Manchester City youngster Phil Foden on loan earlier this summer, claim the Sunday Mirror.
However, the Glasgow club were unsuccessful and the City man looks set to remain at the Etihad for the 2019/20 season.

			
